They say a real friend is one who walks in when the rest of the world walks out. JOHANNESBURG - They say a real friend is one who walks in when the rest of the world walks out. Lindiwe Mhlongo and Matshidiso Mahlatsi -- both in their 70s -- have been inseparable since the age of five. The two have an encyclopaedia of memories, especially from their naughty childhoods. READ: How parents can help their child make and maintain good friendships What's kept their bond so strong is that they're honest with each other. The besties celebrated World Friendship Day on Tuesday and had some words of wisdom on the secret to a long and genuine friendship. The two say it's about having fun and respecting each other.